1
00:00:05,392 --> 00:00:10,448
As usual the children put on a play at the end of term.
孩子们照例在期末上演话剧

2
00:00:10,944 --> 00:00:13,376
John wrote this year's play.
约翰写今年的话剧

3
00:00:13,504 --> 00:00:14,496
Here it is.
是这样的

4
00:00:14,592 --> 00:00:15,872
The bird
鸟

5
00:00:16,848 --> 00:00:20,192
Scene one: A market stall
第一幕   一个街市档位

6
00:00:23,776 --> 00:00:27,936
Birds for sale. Birds for sale. They all sing beautifully.
卖鸟了   卖鸟了   它们都唱得很动听

7
00:00:27,930 --> 00:00:29,248
How much is that bird?
那只鸟多少钱

8
00:00:29,376 --> 00:00:30,224
This yellow one?
这只黄色的吗

9
00:00:30,304 --> 00:00:30,720
Yes.
是的

10
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:31,744
Thirty dollars.
三十美元

11
00:00:31,824 --> 00:00:32,672
And the cage?
笼子呢

12
00:00:32,768 --> 00:00:37,344
Fifty dollars. You can have the bird and the cage for sixty-five dollars.
五十美元   鸟和笼子一共六十五美元卖你

13
00:00:37,408 --> 00:00:38,400
Does the bird sing?
鸟唱歌吗

14
00:00:38,448 --> 00:00:39,792
Of course it does.
当然了

15
00:00:39,888 --> 00:00:42,784
Here you are. Here's sixty-five dollars. 
给你   这是六十五美元

16
00:00:45,216 --> 00:00:49,632
Scene two: Inside the old man's flat
第二幕   在老人的公寓里

17
00:00:51,472 --> 00:00:53,488
What have you got there?
你拿的是什么啊

18
00:00:53,616 --> 00:00:56,208
A bird. I bought it in the market.
一只鸟   我在市场买的

19
00:00:56,352 --> 00:00:58,464
We haven't got enough money for a bird.
我们没钱养鸟

20
00:00:58,576 --> 00:01:01,472
We need lots of things but we don't need a bird.
我们需要很多东西   但我们不需要一只鸟

21
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:04,544
I can take it for a walk in its cage every day.
我可以每天提着笼子带它去散步

22
00:01:04,592 --> 00:01:05,856
It'll sing to me.
它会对我唱歌

23
00:01:05,984 --> 00:01:08,992
You're a silly old man. You waste our money.
你真是个傻老头   你浪费了我们的钱

24
00:01:09,200 --> 00:01:11,968
Don't you like listening to a bird sing?
你难道不喜欢听鸟唱歌吗

25
00:01:12,096 --> 00:01:16,192
I like eating a bird more! Why didn't you buy a chicken or a duck?
我更喜欢吃鸟   你为什么不买只鸡或鸭呢

26
00:01:16,304 --> 00:01:18,336
Because they don't sing.
因为它们不唱歌

27
00:01:19,296 --> 00:01:24,656
Scene three: Inside the flat- two weeks later
第三幕   在公寓里   两周后

28
00:01:25,360 --> 00:01:27,616
That bird hasn't sung yet.
那只鸟还没唱歌呢

29
00:01:27,776 --> 00:01:31,232
I know. And I've taken it for a walk every day. 
我知道   而且我已经每天带它去散步了

30
00:01:31,376 --> 00:01:32,960
Is there anything wrong with it?
它有什么问题吗

31
00:01:33,056 --> 00:01:34,448
I don't know.
我不知道

32
00:01:34,688 --> 00:01:39,376
What a waste of money! Sixty-five dollars for that bird and it won't sing.
多浪费钱啊   六十五美元买那只鸟   还不会唱歌

33
00:01:39,584 --> 00:01:42,064
I'll take it for one more walk.
我再带它去散个步

34
00:01:43,232 --> 00:01:46,528
Scene four: On the street
第四幕   在街上

35
00:01:50,320 --> 00:01:51,760
Good morning, sir.
早上好   先生

36
00:01:51,856 --> 00:01:52,848
Good morning.
早上好

37
00:01:53,056 --> 00:01:55,968
You've got a fine bird in that cage.
你笼子里的鸟真漂亮

38
00:01:56,096 --> 00:01:58,416
Yes, but it won't sing.
是的   但它不唱歌

39
00:01:58,480 --> 00:02:02,496
It won't sing! I can make it sing.
它不会唱歌   我可以让它唱歌

40
00:02:02,560 --> 00:02:03,488
How?
如何

41
00:02:03,696 --> 00:02:07,120
Put it down, sir, next to my bowl.
把它放下   先生   放在我的碗边上

42
00:02:07,488 --> 00:02:15,280
The beggar whistles to the bird and it begins to sing.
乞丐对鸟吹口哨   它开始唱歌

43
00:02:19,296 --> 00:02:21,248
I can't whistle like that.
我不能像那样吹口哨

44
00:02:21,360 --> 00:02:23,376
The bird will never sing for me.
鸟不会为我歌唱了

45
00:02:23,488 --> 00:02:26,720
Then why not give it to me, sir?
那为什么不把它给我呢   先生

46
00:02:27,120 --> 00:02:30,320
It will sing for me every day.
它会每天为我歌唱

47
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:33,536
You can come and listen to it.
你可以过来听

48
00:02:33,616 --> 00:02:35,888
That's a very good idea.
那是个非常好的主意

49
00:02:38,688 --> 00:02:41,808
Scene five: Inside the flat
第五幕   在公寓里

50
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:43,984
Where's the bird?
鸟在哪儿

51
00:02:44,128 --> 00:02:47,072
I gave it to the beggar on the corner of the street.
我把它给了街角的那个乞丐

52
00:02:47,424 --> 00:02:51,888
You gave it to the beggar! Why did you do that?
你把它给了那个乞丐   你为什么这样做

53
00:02:52,032 --> 00:02:53,888
Because it'll sing for him.
因为它会为他歌唱

54
00:02:54,752 --> 00:02:57,888
You gave that beggar sixty-five dollars!
你给了那个乞丐六十五美元

55
00:02:58,160 --> 00:03:04,896
You don't understand. The bird won't sing for me but it will sing for him.
你不懂   鸟不会为我歌唱   但它会为他歌唱

56
00:03:05,232 --> 00:03:07,904
I can listen to it every day now.
现在我可以每天听了

57
00:03:08,320 --> 00:03:11,408
But it's not your bird now. It's his.
但它现在不是你的鸟了啊   是他的了

58
00:03:11,808 --> 00:03:14,896
Yes, but it's not his song.
是的   但这不是他的歌

59
00:03:15,248 --> 00:03:20,080
I wanted the song, not the bird. Now I've got it.
我想要的是歌   不是鸟   现在我得到了

60
00:03:20,320 --> 00:03:22,448
You're a very silly old man.
你是个非常傻的老头

61
00:03:22,528 --> 00:03:23,456
Am I?
是吗

